  "prompt": "I want to read about Swami Vivekananda. Tell me one or two good books on Swami Vivekananda?",
  "response": "Certainly! Swami Vivekananda, a key figure in the introduction of Indian philosophies of Vedanta and Yoga to the Western world, has been the subject of numerous books. Here are two highly regarded books that provide insight into his life and teachings:\n\n1. **\"The Life of Swami Vivekananda\" by His Eastern and Western Disciples** - This is a comprehensive biography that gives a detailed account of Swami Vivekananda's life, his travels, teachings, and the impact he had on both Eastern and Western thought. It is considered an authoritative text on his life and is written by those who were close to him or his disciples.\n\n2. **\"Vivekananda: A Biography\" by Swami Nikhilananda** - Swami Nikhilananda was a direct disciple of Sri Sarada Devi, the spiritual consort of Sri Ramakrishna, and a respected monk of the Ramakrishna Order. His biography of Swami Vivekananda is well-researched and provides a deep understanding of Vivekananda's spiritual journey, his association with Sri Ramakrishna, and his mission to spread the message of Vedanta across the world.\n\nBoth books offer valuable insights into the life of Swami Vivekananda and are excellent starting points for anyone looking to learn more about his contributions to spirituality and philosophy.",
